# Patch: ce-compound-smart-mode-select
# Replaces the strict "Do NOT pre-select a mode" prompt with smart mode detection.
#
# Applied by strip-from-upstream.sh using sed.
#
# Before: Always prompts user to choose Full vs Lightweight, even when args
#         clearly signal intent.
# After:  Skips the prompt when user args contain clear signals (harness names,
#         "dig into", "exhaustive" → Full; "quick"/"lightweight" → Lightweight).
#         Bare /ce:compound with no args still always prompts.
